    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_747-772",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "747-772",
      "markText": "我们没有任何知识先行于经验，一切知识都从经验开始。",
      "totalCount": 391,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=747&rangeEnd=772",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=747&rangeEnd=772"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_12_925-954",
      "chapterUid": 12,
      "range": "925-954",
      "markText": "通过我们被对象刺激的方式获得表象的能力（感受性）叫做感性。",
      "totalCount": 350,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=12&rangeStart=925&rangeEnd=954",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=12&rangeStart=925&rangeEnd=954"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_12_712-773",
      "chapterUid": 12,
      "range": "712-773",
      "markText": "无论一种知识以什么方式以及通过什么手段与对象发生关系，它与对象直接发生关系所凭借的以及一切思维当做手段所追求的，就是直观。",
      "totalCount": 299,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=12&rangeStart=712&rangeEnd=773",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=12&rangeStart=712&rangeEnd=773"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_2252-2290",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "2252-2290",
      "markText": "因此必然性和严格的普遍性是一种先天知识的可靠标志，而且也不可分割地相互从属。",
      "totalCount": 266,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2252&rangeEnd=2290",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2252&rangeEnd=2290"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_14950-15100",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "14950-15100",
      "markText": "我把一切不研究对象、而是一般地研究我们关于对象的认识方式———就这种方式是先天地可能的而言———的知识(34)称为先验的。",
      "totalCount": 256,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=14950&rangeEnd=15100",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=14950&rangeEnd=15100"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_2_675-767",
      "chapterUid": 2,
      "range": "675-767",
      "markText": "与经验论伴生的机械唯物主义则把自然科学的研究方法直接挪用到对人和社会的研究，在以“人是机器”为代表的观点下把人的道德、信仰等等统统纳入机械因果关系的范畴，严重地威胁着人类的自由和尊严。",
      "totalCount": 253,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=2&rangeStart=675&rangeEnd=767",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=2&rangeStart=675&rangeEnd=767"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_8_997-1052",
      "chapterUid": 8,
      "range": "997-1052",
      "markText": "因为它所使用的原理既然超越了一切经验的界限，就不再承认经验的试金石。这些无休无止的争吵的战场，就叫做形而上学。",
      "totalCount": 242,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=8&rangeStart=997&rangeEnd=1052",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=8&rangeStart=997&rangeEnd=1052"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_1537-1590",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "1537-1590",
      "markText": "例如“每一变化皆有其原因”这个命题就是一个先天命题，但并不是纯粹的，因为变化是一个只能从经验中取得的概念。",
      "totalCount": 240,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1537&rangeEnd=1590",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1537&rangeEnd=1590"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_2_1138-1186",
      "chapterUid": 2,
      "range": "1138-1186",
      "markText": "康德的哲学不仅使理性论和经验论的争执永远成为历史，而且为哲学、形而上学的发展指明了一个新的方向。",
      "totalCount": 216,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=2&rangeStart=1138&rangeEnd=1186",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=2&rangeStart=1138&rangeEnd=1186"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_2711-2800",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "2711-2800",
      "markText": "以至于如果有人像休谟所做的那样，想从所发生的事情与先行的事情经常的相伴随中、从由此产生的联结种种表象的习惯（从而仅仅是主观的必然性）中引申出这个概念，那么，这个概念就会完全丧失。",
      "totalCount": 216,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2711&rangeEnd=2800",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2711&rangeEnd=2800"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_1021-1049",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "1021-1049",
      "markText": "是否有一种这样独立于经验、甚至独立于一切感官印象的知识。",
      "totalCount": 210,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1021&rangeEnd=1049",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1021&rangeEnd=1049"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_1754-1787",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "1754-1787",
      "markText": "经验虽然告诉我们某物是如此这般，但却没有告诉我们它不能是别的样子。",
      "totalCount": 210,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1754&rangeEnd=1787",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1754&rangeEnd=1787"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_13_2076-2120",
      "chapterUid": 13,
      "range": "2076-2120",
      "markText": "空间不是一个关于一般事物的关系的推理概念，或者如人们所说是一个普遍概念，而是一个纯直观。",
      "totalCount": 192,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=13&rangeStart=2076&rangeEnd=2120",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=13&rangeStart=2076&rangeEnd=2120"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_2062-2127",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "2062-2127",
      "markText": "因此，如果一个判断在严格的普遍性上被思维，也就是说，根本不允许任何例外是可能的，那么，它就不是由经验派生的，而是绝对先天地有效的。",
      "totalCount": 180,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2062&rangeEnd=2127",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2062&rangeEnd=2127"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_3_1940-2039",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "1940-2039",
      "markText": "人类的认识（Erkenntnis）具有两个主干，它们也许出自共同的，尚不为所知的根基，这就是感性（Sinnlichkeit）和知性（Verstand） 。通过前者对象被给予我们，通过后者它们被思想。",
      "totalCount": 176,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1940&rangeEnd=2039",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1940&rangeEnd=2039"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_3_3407-3472",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "3407-3472",
      "markText": "空间是外感觉的形式，一切外在经验中的对象都在空间中排列着，伸延着。时间是内感觉的形式，一切思想和概念的活动都先后连续着在时间中运行",
      "totalCount": 168,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=3407&rangeEnd=3472",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=3407&rangeEnd=3472"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_10_1419-1470",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "1419-1470",
      "markText": "不是把先天知识理解为不依赖于这个或者那个经验而发生的知识，而是理解为绝对不依赖于一切经验而发生的知识。",
      "totalCount": 168,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1419&rangeEnd=1470",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=1419&rangeEnd=1470"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "26392183_12_1324-1379",
      "chapterUid": 12,
      "range": "1324-1379",
      "markText": "在显象中，我把与感觉相应的东西称为显象的质料，而把使得显象的杂多能够在某些关系中得到整理的东西称为显象的形式。",
      "totalCount": 168,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=26392183&chapterUid=12&rangeStart=1324&rangeEnd=1379",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/e0132f607192b677e018b46?chapterUid=12&rangeStart=1324&rangeEnd=1379"
    }
